0. Basic Definitions.

  "Covered Work" means the Received Work or a Derived Work.

  "Derived Work" means a work of authorship that copies from,
  modifies, adapts, is based on, contains, transforms or translates
  all or part of the Received Work such that copyright permission is
  required. Derived Works do not include Mere Aggregation or the mere
  making of a verbatim copy of the Received Work.

  "Distribute" means to transfer or make available a copy to someone
  else (in the case of an organization, to someone outside of the
  organization), such that copyright permission is required.

  "Distributor" means Us and anyone else who Distributes a Covered
   Work.

  "Mere Aggregation" means an aggregation of a Covered Work with a
  Separate Work. However, if the license of such an aggregation
  restricts users from exercising rights in the Covered Work given by
  this License, the aggregation is not Mere Aggregation.

  "Received Work" means the particular work of authorship We license
  to you under this License.

  "Separate Work" means a work that is separate from and independent
  of a particular Covered Work and is not by its nature an extension
  or enhancement of the Covered Work.

  "We"/"Us"/"Our" refers to the individual or organization that places
  the Received Work under this License.

