8. Object Code Distribution.

8.1. General Definitions.

     "Minimum Period", with respect to a Covered Work embodied in a
     Product, means the longer of (i) two years from the date of your
     Distribution of the Covered Work in the Product, or (ii) the
     period during which you offer spare parts or customer support for
     the Product.

     "Object Code" means any form of a work that is not Source Code.

     "Product" means a physical product or tangible storage medium.

     "Source Code" means the preferred form of a work for making
     modifications to it.

     "System Libraries" means [FIXME].

8.2. Definition of Corresponding Source.
  
     "Corresponding Source" of a Covered Work means all the Source
     Code needed to build, compile, generate, modify, install, and run
     the Covered Work, to the extent those activities are meaningful
     ("Development Activities"). Corresponding Source must be in
     machine-readable form.

     Corresponding Source includes (i) all relevant scripts and
     instructions known to you (even if previously unrecorded)
     necessary for a skilled person to effectively perform, control
     and/or complete Development Activities; (ii) interface definition
     files; and (iii) the Source Code of shared libraries and
     dynamically-linked subprograms that the Covered Work is
     specifically designed to require, such as by intimate data
     communication or control flow between those subprograms and parts
     of the Covered Work.

     Corresponding Source does not include (i) a Separate Work used in
     performing Development Activities, or (ii) the Covered Work's
     System Libraries.

8.3. Conditions for Distributing Object Code.

     You may Distribute a Covered Work in Object Code form, provided
     that:

     a. For Object Code Distributed in a Product: you accompany the
        Product with either:

        1) a durable physical medium customarily used for software
           interchange that contains the Corresponding Source, or

        2) notice of a network location through which the
           Corresponding Source is available under this License at no
           charge, for the Minimum Period.

     b. For Object Code Distributed from a network location: you
        accompany the Object Code with clear directions indicating how
        the Corresponding Source may be obtained under this License
        from a network location at no further charge and in a
        reasonably equivalent manner.

