10. Termination.

10.1. If you fail to comply with the conditions of this License, then,
      unless you cure such violations of this License within thirty
      days after becoming aware of them, your license grants under
      section 1 are automatically terminated.

10.2. If you initiate litigation by asserting a patent infringement
      claim (excluding declaratory judgment actions, counterclaims,
      and cross-claims) alleging that any part of the Received Work
      directly or indirectly infringes any patent, then your license
      grants under section 1 are automatically terminated.

10.3. Termination of your rights disqualifies you from receiving new
      licenses covering the Received Work. It does not terminate the
      rights of those who have received copies or rights from you
      subject to this License.

10.4. Your right to make copies necessarily incident to running
      Covered Works shall never be terminated.

